<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="118" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Female. Frons with 68–70 setulae; 2 supra-antennal setae shorter and thinner than adjacent setae; apical seta as long as maximum width of palpus; flagellomere 1 bean-shaped, arista short; vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1157,1182,314,328]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">2+3</subScript>
absent; fore tarsomere 5 long, tapered; setal palisade 3/4 length of mid tibia; 8 postero-dorsal setulae on hind tibia; tergite VI rectangular, with 10 short setulae at rear margin; sternite VI divided into two small irregular pieces, each with 3–4 setulae; oviscape parallel sided.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Female</emphasis>
. Body length 
<quantity box="[449,553,439,466]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="0.95">0.95 mm</quantity>
. Frons (
<figureCitation box="[646,736,439,465]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) brown, with 68–70 setulae. One pair of supra-antennal setae short and thin, 0.6 times as long as adjacent frontal setae. Lower interfrontal seta closer to median furrow than to eye margin. First row of frontal setae slightly convex on frons. Second row of frontal setae concave, upper interfrontal setae further from each other than either is to an upper fronto-orbital seta. Flagellomere 1 brown, bean-shaped and pointed at apex; arista short. Palpus pale brown, with 4 long setae, apical one is as long as maximum width of palpus. Labrum light brown and triangular. Labella light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
Thorax brown. Scutellum with two pairs of setae, posterior three times length of anterior. Legs brown, hind femora being darkest. Ratios of lengths of fore tarsomeres about 0.99: 0.63: 0.59: 0.51: 1; tarsomere 5 slender and tapered (
<figureCitation box="[250,336,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
). Dorsal setal palisade extends 3/4 length of mid tibia (
<figureCitation box="[959,1049,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); tarsomere 5 slender and tapered; ratios of lengths of mid tarsomeres about 1.67: 0.71: 0.63: 0.59: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[919,1009,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
). Setae below basal half of hind femur longer and thicker than those of anteroventral setulae of outer half (
<figureCitation box="[924,1013,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
); setal palisade extends 9/10 of tibia; hind tibia with 8 postero-dorsal setulae; tarsomere 5 tapered (
<figureCitation box="[845,934,835,861]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) but not as same as that in fore tarsomere 5, ratios of lengths of hind tarsomeres about 2.75: 0.88: 0.88: 0.75: 1 (
<figureCitation box="[956,1048,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
). Wing (
<figureCitation box="[1146,1233,871,897]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) length 
<quantity box="[1328,1432,871,898]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="0.87">0.87 mm</quantity>
, width 
<quantity box="[221,323,907,934]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="0.42">0.42 mm</quantity>
, width/length 0.48. Costal index 0.32. Vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[830,855,926,940]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">2+3</subScript>
absent. Costal ratios 1.42: 1. Costal cilia 
<quantity box="[1323,1437,907,934]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" unit="mm" value="0.034">0.034 mm</quantity>
long. Costa with 11–12 dorsal setulae. Alula with 2 setae. Veins brown, membrane brownish gray. Haltere brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
Abdominal tergites brown and tergites I–V with sparse minute setulae on posterior margins. Tergite VI (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2J</figureCitation>
) approximately rectangular, with about 10 setulae at rear margin, of which 4 are longer. Venter brown. Sternite VI (
<figureCitation box="[197,287,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2K</figureCitation>
) divided into two small irregular pieces, each bearing 3–4 long setulae. Ovipositor parallel sided, the dorsum apex of the oviscape with about 15–16 minute setulae each side and the venter apex of the oviscape with 10–12 minute setulae (
<figureCitation box="[406,485,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1892,1916]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,179,1865]" captionTargetId="figure-22@4.[151,1435,179,1867]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2A–K. Microselia yanjingensis sp. nov., female. A. head, anterior view; B. wing, dorsal view; C. mid tibia, posterior view; D. hind tibia, posterior view; E. hind femur, anterior view; F. fore tarsus, posterior view; G. mid tarsus, posterior view; H. hind tarsus, posterior view; I. ovipositor, dorsal view; J. tergite VI; K. sternite VI. Scale bar = 0.1mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6825697" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6825697/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Fig. 2I</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" box="[199,392,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,1159,1185]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Male.</emphasis>
Unkonwn.
</paragraph>
