<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,259,1510]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1375,1401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Disney, 1988" authorityName="Disney" authorityYear="1988" box="[649,1058,1375,1401]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Microselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="southwoodi">
<emphasis box="[649,905,1375,1401]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">Microselia southwoodi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Disney, R. H. L." box="[911,1058,1375,1401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" pagination="85 - 88" refId="ref2879" refString="Disney, R. H. L. (1988) A new species of Microselia (Dipt. Phoridae) from France. Annales de Parasitologie Humaine et Comparee, 63, 85 - 88. https: // doi. org / 10.1051 / parasite / 198863185" type="journal article" year="1988">
Disney, 
<quantity box="[1002,1058,1375,1401]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.04952" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" unit="in" value="1988.0">1988</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of the form of ovipositor and absence of vein R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[403,428,1430,1444]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">2+3</subScript>
. It is differs from the latter by less setulae of frons, shorter supra-antennal setae and less postero-setulae of hind tibia. It is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Liu, 2022" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2022" box="[755,908,1447,1473]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Microselia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longarista" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[755,908,1447,1473]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">M. longarista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[916,1007,1447,1473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[916,1007,1447,1473]" pageId="3" pageNumber="118" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by less frons setulae, less and shorter supra-antennal setae, shorter setae of palpus, bean-shaped flagellomere 1 and shorter arista.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
